COPS nabbed him in a dirty brothel. And the suspect has appeared in court to face serious charges involving sexual offences and trafficking in persons.Charles Okopie (34) from Nigeria was detained by the Hawks last week in a pre-dawn raid on a building in Klerksdorp, North West. They charged him after getting a tip-off. The cops rescued 26 South African women and children between 14 and 37 years of age. They also took 19 men in for questioning. He will appear again next Wednesday to apply for bail. Captain Tlangelani Rikhotso of the North West Hawks told the People&rsquo;s Paper: &ldquo;He was arrested following a statement by one of the women, alleging his involvement in running a brothel.&rdquo;